<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17317] JAX-RS v2 APIs return XML when wt=json specified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17317</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A mailing list user recently pointed out that certain JAX-RS v2 APIs return XML content when &quot;wt=json&quot; is specified!  The cause is an embarrassing oversight in &quot;V2ApiUtils.getMediaTypeFromWtParam&quot;: a switch-case statement there accidentally omits &quot;json&quot; from its list of supported &quot;wt&quot; values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add the missing branch of the switch-case block, and validate that v2 APIs now respond correctly when wt=json is specified.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
